text:
I have stayed with this amazing couple, Max and Katia, for two nights. They are really welcoming and caring hosts. They are very attentive to their guest and provide them with everything that a traveller may need. Max and Katia are true Couchsurfers, they praise and relish the idea of Couchsurfing. 
I enjoyed my stay with them and I wish them the best of luck in bringing their ideas to life!

Max accepted to host me and my girlfriend even though it's our first time on CS, he was very friendly, thoughtful and very kind. We had our plans changed, and he didn't mind hosting us for another night. It was a big pleasure to stay with Max and his wife Kate, we had interesting talks about our countries and many things. I would love to meet him again !! Hopefully soon my friend :D

Max and Kate are really nice hosts. They were really friendly and nice. They showed us the city and we had a lot of interesting conversations. Since Max had his birthday one day before we arrived, we made some Brazilian sweeties as a tradition and we knew that he loves sweet. It was really nice to stay with them, I recommend for everyone!

Max and his wife Kate are absolutely amazing. We had great conversations, he showed us the city, and shared many stories of Ukraine. 
Fernanda and I had an awesome time with them in Kharkiv and I hope to see them soon again :)

Max and Katia were amazing hosts in Kharkiv, they made the stay so memorable!

They were very friendly, and told many interesting and unique stories about themselves, about Ukraine and about traveling. We were also invited to spend time at an ingress social event, which was unexpected but great fun! The stay was very special, and I would definitely count Max and Katia as good friends, even after just three nights, as we chatted for ages about all sorts of things. Max was extremely helpful in making sure we got to the home, and we felt completely welcome the whole time we were staying in the house.

The city centre is easily accessible by bus, the train station is a little far by foot if you do not want to walk, but completely worth it for the secret amazing view over the city from Max's neighbourhood! 

I am super thankful to Max and Katia for making our stay so special, and I would really advise everyone to stay with them when in Kharkiv!

We've had great times together, chilling out or having more serious talks. We shared our visions and experiences of life under many aspects. She is cultured, open-minded and sincere in her quest of beauty and sense in life. 
And I've been lucky enough to see her in action in two of her (many and various) talents : make-up artist and photographer. More precisely, I've had the chance to witness her in action when finding beauty in the world, empowering it and make it visible to our eyes. It was astonishing and magnificent. She really is special. She really is beautiful. 
Not mentioning she is a great guest, generous and showing much respect for the house and her hosts, knowing when to keep company and when to be on her own too. 
She gave A LOT and I'm not the only one who received that much when hosting her, because my Dad who met her already asked me: "when does Anna come back?" 
I wish many Couchsurfers to meet Anna...

I have hosted Sergey for a house concert at my place. It has been a great experience for me and for many of my guests of the event. Sergey's life, at the moment, is about music, art and traveling. His performance itself is a summary of his long trip around many places he has been doing since about four years now: his pics, his videos and his music are a summary of the experiences he has had all around the world . He is a very friendly and an easy going guy with an independent spirit. He seems to be very much able to enjoy the moment with a very quiet but sensitive approach. As a guest he has been kind and relaxed about everything. I really recommnend to meet or to host him!!!

Sergey is too modest for the great things he's done so far in his life. I only received insipiration from the way he lives and from what we talked about (travelling, nutrition) and I am very grateful to him for having spent a beautiful peaceful day around, talking. My too little sons had a great time with him, too. He gave a small lesson of photography on the lake to my son. The concert was really beautiful, like a flying trip over far away high mountains, rivers and oceans. He involves people from the public in playing rare instruments and everything turns out in an unique and unforgettable experience for everyone.

He's a really nice human being, full of experiences and art.. we shared some super tasty salad and hot carubbas tea, and the concert was really enlightening. 
Have a nice trip man! Was nice to hear some of your experiences :)

text: Aye aye, Captain... beware all you folks of this wayward pirate or else thou shall be infected by the love and energy contained within his most exquisite musical composition!!! I was booked out for Serg to stay aboard, but in the end, my little sail boat made for two people was loaded to the brims with 5 CSers in the most epic evening I ever had on CS. We all certainly brought "something" to the table, but Serg's unique soul was certainly what made that evening so special. Words are not neeeded, nor are they enough. "Next time we meet, the rum is on me... one for you and one for the Gods at sea".

text: I was getting ready for a short travel to the South Island. I was pretty excited dreaming about it when I got Sergey¬¥s couch request. ¬®Life is unfair!¬® I thought. How come i¬¥m not going to be in Wellington to host this amazing creature that is coming with loads of musical plans, a guitar, and his band name has the word ¬®tree¬® in it???!! So...as soon as i came back to Welli I wrote him. Hopefully Sergey was still having gigs around the city so we met one night, and the next one he was sleeping on our lounge, jamming with all sorts of people in the guitar workshop, and bonding with our rabbit (that NEVER allows anyone to touch her). He was magic, and everybody noticed that. I hope you have a great time down South, that you always find a hot soup, and that you find the warmest couch in the world. text:
I'm sorry to not have the same feeling of you. You are happy to stayed in my home,i am happy you feel good. but come on man, you didn't do couchsurfing you do like a guest house, taking rest, washing clothes, using internet, and cook WITHOUT WASHING THE DISHES. 
You tell you speak with me and my girlfriends, REALLY, WHEN ??? in 2 days we talk maybe only 1 h and you was just interest about where to take some stuff. 
I really feel that you were better go to guest house (cambodia you can find room for 4$ - 5$ even less) because we didn't have any conversation together, i know the second days you try a bit but it was too late. 
I host you because i wanted to make discover couchsurfing spirit to my khmers girlfriends and her baby who dosen't understand WHY i host foreigner in my home for free and she was very angry with you to not come eat with us even if we don't eat the same things, this is khmers culture !!!! and you didn't respect it, more than culture i think it was the minimum to do.

text:
Sergey is one hell of a cool guy. He stayed in my small apartment for 2 days and I was sad to see him leave. A very talented musician, he played three concerts (two impromptu, one organized) at different bars and events around the city and got the crowds on fire every time :) Also, even though he travels frugally (hitch-hiking, stretching his money however he can) he is a generous soul, and gave away many of his beautiful artsy photographs or DIY music CDs to my friends and I. He told me really cool stories about his travels and taught me stuff about Russian artists, something I'm interested in.

The only thing is that he should change his profile picture to something more upbeat, because in real life he smiles way more! :)

I dont want you to get too much requests for the Europcup next year Sergey, so i will stop here - Just a big Thanks to you. You are always welcome wherever I can provide you a couch.

text:
Sergiy is really amazing hoster! This guy is the one who'll show you a lot of great places in Kharkiv because he's really know and love his city. And you'll like conversation with him! Sergiy is fun, positive and considerate person, you'll never get bored when he's around. 
In his home you'll feel sincere affection and comfort. His mother cooking perfectly, it's unforgettable :)

I spend just 3 days in Kharkiv, but I already fell in love with Ukrain. 
Sergey is not just a wonderful cook, but also a wonderful musican (you have to see his collection of flutes!). We played music together, he showed me around and introduced me to friends. 
He helped me to buy a bike (Sputnik for ever!) and gave me great travel information about his country.
If it happens he comes to your city, don`t miss to host him. He is full of funny and intresting stories and music from all over the world.
Thanks a lot for sharing your home with me!

I'm sure you haven't seen a lot in this small and cozy city.
See you!
Svetlana and her friend Daria were really nice and friendly,  we hang out a little and I wish we could spend more time chatting.  I can recommend anyone to host Svetlana :)

text: She is perfect. She always help me. If you want to explore area , she can help you. If you haven‚Äôt place for stay, she can be host.  I like her cats and her house is very clean. She is friendly and she is cheerful. Thank you for everything Matsibora!

Unfortunately, Svetlana's lovely cats refused all attempts to speak in Spanish or English so communication with them was quite difficult. Also, one of them stole my chapstick for two days but returned it before I left. Her friend Daria does speak good English and did not steal any chapstick. Daria is super fun to hang out with and I only wish I'd had more time to explore the area or go listen to music with them. Sveta herself is not the best guitar player but she is an amazing host with a great sense of humor and unmatched generosity.  I could not have enjoyed my time more or learned more about her city. Her home is cozy and not far from HRK.  (Also, they love small gifts like delicious foods or alcohol from your country.))
She is very kind , intelligent and easy going person. I like to have conversation with her. I advice you can stay with her . Thank you for your warm friendship Sveta. Good luck !

She is very helpful, cheerful girl.

It was nice to spend  time with Svetlana, i got good impression about Kharkiv:)

Sveta is great. she is very funny and interesting. knows and tells a lot about the city, recommends mega interesting places and is ready to show the city. we stopped at her with a friend and everything was very cozy and friendly. Sveta brings a lot of energy everywhere she goes. She is a fun person to be around, has a good home, lovely cats, genuine spirit and knows all the graffiti in Kharkiv! It was a total blast from every angle. If you're in Kharkiv and want something real, she's your gal!

Svetlana is are very friendly and easy kind of person. There are was second time when i stay with her, and this was great as always. That time Svetlana tell me that she like horror movies and we had saw two or three of them. If you like horror movies - tell about that to Svet

Svetlana is pleasant, easy-going person and a caring host.  She showed us interesting places around the city and in the evening we watched horror movies together.
  Sveta likes travelling as much as she loves to host and has a lot of interesting stories to tell. We had a great time with her!

Just a short message to thank you Svetlana, you are a true living example of what hospitality, friendliness & fun mean- I was delighted to spend this time with you and your lovely friend Dacha, and thanks a lot also for showing me around the city :)
Warmest, 
Cheers+++

Svetlana is a ray of cosmic starlight in anyone's life, if you happen to cross paths with her, that is.  She has the most quirky and loveable personality, coupled with thoughtfulness and a pair of quite irresistible lady cats. Even if you are not a fan of cats you will find hundreds of topics to discuss with her, or none at all, if you choose, since she respects the concept of private space . All in all, she is a great host and guest.  And she will laugh at the least funny jokes, so it's easy to entertain her;)

Svetlana it's positive and happy people, she showed me a city and she knows how to make a great Ukrainian soup.
I recommend to all surfers in Kharkiv. Thanks!

me and my friend spent one night in svetlana's cute house. she was so friendly and caring. hope to see her somewhere else.

Sveta is so unusual person. Interesting, open and friendly.

Thank you for tasty home food, roof and interesting life stories.

Don't lose the chance to meet and have nice time with Sveta. She is really cool.

Very warm friendly girl who generously hosted for a couple of weeks in her little "cat house", even had whole house for a while. Despite our short stay and Sasha's/Dariia's busy schedule, we had the opportunity to hang out several times all together. Sasha and Dariia showed us the city, and introduced some of their friends to us¬† ; meeting them was very interesting for us.

Dariia and Sasha are also very interesting when it comes to deep discussions. They are both curious about everything, asking many questions. Thanks to them, we learned a lot of details and anecdotes regarding Ukraine and the life of ukrainian people in general.

Last but not least, we enjoyed a very good Omelette they cooked just before we left =).

Gauthier and me are happy to now consider Dariia and Sasha as friends. We are grateful for everything they did for us, and it will be a great pleasure to meet with them again!

I am really grateful for being able to see Kharkiv from her perspective as well as staying at her place where I could meet her two lovely cats. Olena is a very open and friendly person. She is very hospitable and helpful. 
I hope she will decide to visit Poland one day as I would be very happy to host her and show her my town.
Meeting and staying at Olena's place was a wonderful experience for me. Thank you!

Olena perfectly embodies that ever-elusive Couchsurfing spirit. She welcomed me into her home, cooked me a meal, offered me some good conversation, and let me sleep on the kitchen floor. That was really nice couple of days when I stayed in Olena's place. She is really fun  and smart person. I can really recommend here as a host and friend! Xoxo

Thank you so much for being so considerate, for helping carrying heavy stuff from the last floor (and still managing to smile :-) and for bringing perfect presents. I hope to see you again in Austria or Ukraine!

My first impression of Kharkiv was positive and unique thanks to Rustam! He's an absolutely authentic and friendly guy, welcomed me with open arms and was kind enough to meet me at the station upon my arrival.¬†Apart from sharing our life stories, different¬† travel experience and¬†songs, he invited me to his friend's Caucasus dance class(the most fun and craziest dance class I've attended while travelling!!) and organised a chilled tea circle which I¬†was kindly invited to joinüëç¬†As a skilled drum player, he will make sure you keep the right beat while exploring vibrant Kharkiv, thank you Rustam!

Stayed at her place when was in Kharkiv and it was great time. Elena showed me the city, it was excursion with many interesting stories and funny jokes. She kindly showed me memorable places of Kharkiv and great park with cool rides where we screamed a lot. Elena is a person with whom you can talk at night sitting at windowsill and drink tea or "Petrovskaya Sloboda" (don`t ask me what it is more, coffee or tea, cause I don`t know). She is funny, clever, polite, friendly and open-minded.

Her place is very clean, situated near the subway station, so you can easily ride to any point of the city.

Hope to see her again!

Even when Elena can't host me in their own house, she was helped me and find the flat of her friend, who can accommodate me. Also we very good and with fun spent time together with she and her friends. Thank you so much, Lena! :)

Lena is a wonderful person. She showed me everything that everyone should see in Kharkov. Especially I remember the Kharkov baking "Kulinichi" and the bookstore "Knigarnya E". Lena is very cheerful and sincere. She travels a lot around Ukraine and she has something to tell about her adventures. Day in the city thanks to her passed unnoticed.

Petro hosted me two nights in his flat located next to metro station. He offered for me separated room in sovet style flat which I really enjoyed. We have nice talk at the evening. I highly recommend his company. Petro, you are welcome in Krakow asap.
I stayed in Vladyslav place during one night. He is very hospitality and kind man. We spent a good time, I would recommend host or stay with Vlad.

It was a pleasure to host Igor and two of his children, Maria and Piotr.  Igor and I did not share any common language but Maria is an excellent translator and Piotr speaks English too. They are very good people and both Maria and Piotr are a credit to their parents, if only all youngsters were so well behaved, happy and sociable. Piotr was the official sandwich maker during the stay and Maria who has almost finished her ballet studies answered all the myriad of questions I had about life in the world of ballet... fascinating.

Don't forget you are welcome back anytime you wish to visit Poznan and maybe I will find time to drop in if I get the chance to visit Kharkov as now I know 6 CSers from that city. :)
Igor with his Don Was my guests  .They were no terrible , nice  nad conciderate with a sens of humor

I was impressed by knowledge what Ihor have about city! We see whole city, monuments, parks, museums and all interesting historical places.

So now I feel like a citizen of Kharkiv :) Thank you!

And more he helped me when I get in troubles in Kiev. Call his friend and he helped me too.

For sure I will back to Kharkiv and stay onece again with Ihor and his family's. Because i feel like in home there..

Thank you for all! Get in touch!

My Alex...He hosted me for 2 nights , and that 2 days were my best times in Kharkiv indeed.  He did everything for me to feel really comfortable and feel at home. I really would LOVE to travel with him , one day. I am very very happy I have a friend like Alex. I really thank to you , my Alex. I wish to meet you again , in Ukraine , in Turkey or somewhere in the world. Kisses.

text:
Vladyslav and his girlfriend are really sweet people and I'm happy they hosted me. We didn't spend much time together, but they were really friendly and nice to me. Even their cat was pretty sweet not to scratch me and spent whole night walking around (probably, she was curious about new person :). I can't stop telling they're nice and sweet, because they're really nice and sweet!  
Thank you, you'll definitely have the tickets on me ;)

It was a relaxed experience staying with Vladyslav and his girlfriend Tanja. As he said, they are usually on the other side of the couch, so they were understanding hosts. I got time and space to do some work, and got to see the city as well.
We talked a bit about politics and travels as well. I'd definitely recommend staying with them if you find yourself headed to Kharkiv.
Thank you!

I was lucky enough to meet Vlad and his girlfriend . Vlad is a super host, friendly, kind, easygoing, gentle guy. 
I definitely recommend him and would meet him again. 

Thank you Vlad for the great hosting experience!

Vlad is a friend of a couchsurfer I met right before going to Ukraine and Russia. My guest contacted Vlad to see if he could help me and he was very accommodating to help me and He did! I run into some issues with time but he was very polite and patient. Such a cool couple. He lives with his girlfriend in a nice apt near the center! We shared stories about trips and life in general, and how they are planning to travel more and more! Vlad if you ever come to Boston, hit me up, if I am there, I will definitely help you out! Thank you so much again! Udachiii!!! :)

My friend and I have stayed with Vlad for 3 days. He is very friendly, affable, he has a great sense of humor and he is just a cool guy. Vlad has visited a lot of places, that's why he has in store a lot of interesting stories. I am sure if you have an opportunity to meet this guy, you won't get dissappointed :)

Igor is very friendly and easy to talk to.He is amazing gueast to host.I hope we meet again :)
Igor is an easy-going person with an entrepreneurial spirit. He stayed at my place for one night; I wish we had more chance to talk.

Even stayed 3/4 nights in my house, we didn't spend to much time together because i work all the days and usually Igor arrive only at midnight at my place. He seems to be friendly, energic and curious guy.
Igor was a good guest. He stayed one night with me, and as I had work, was happy to go into the city and do his own thing. It was interesting to hear about his life in New York, and all his travels
Igor is a friendly and energetic person. He's very curious about the world. He arrived late and left very early in the morning, so we were unable to spend much time together.

I'm glad that I hosted Igor. He has interesting energetic personality and can share with many stories and experience that he had. I think everybody would take something new from Igor. Also I enjoyed how easy-going and straightforward he is. Keep going, bro!

I would gladly host Igor again, mostly because I hardly ever got to see him. That said, based on our brief interaction, Igor is definitely a kind soul with an adventurous spirit and someone I have no problems recommending to other hosts/surfers.

He is fun, happy go person, friendly, trying hard to communicate English fluently but will sustain a good conversation. There is no dull moment with him, he fills the gap if you are in a group.  I am totally impressed with his CS venture at his age, visited 30 or more different places in different countries. I wish I had his courage to jump from one place to another using today's hot spot internet sites. Hats off to you my friend. You are more than welconebto my home.

Igor sent me last call request from the airport, because air company sold out more tickets that plane can contain. And I just coudn't ignore this situation: I had a free time and apartment to welcome. So he was living in my flat for two days before another plane brought him to NY city.  During this time I got only positive things about Igor. He's a tactful, intelligent, friendly and open mind person.  I think  you'll conclude the same if meet him someday on your road.

Igor is a very flexible and spontaneous guy who likes to send last-minute couch request. lol. It is also my first acceptance of this kind. He is very talktive, and ambitious about what he is doing. We had some interesting conversation,though he only stayed for one night. And his cellphone clock managed to keep me suffering in the early morning. Wish u the best :)

I was the first address for Igor in Jerusalem. Igor is a very humble person, and as well thoughtful to my needs as well as I was to his. His staying, although it was short, was pleasent for me and I hope for him to.

Igor contacted me last minute (about 9:30pm), as his host bailed on him last minute for some personal reason.
Having been in the same position a few times abroad while travelling, I've invited him over and we've had a fun night drinking, eating, chatting and exchanging languages. He left early the next morning to continue his excursion through Israel.

Igor - You're living the dream - travelling all over the world; I envy you, buddy! I hope you'll come back to visit one day!
If not, see you somewhere on the globe - may it be Ukraine, USA or Dubai (I wish...)!

I stayed two nights with Lili and her friend. Both of them are absolutely wonderful people and I'm glad that I met them along my journey. It was really nice to spent some time together and to talk about our adventures. Their apartment is located really close to the center of Kharkiv, so it was perfect to explore the city. Lili's friend Anthon knows probalbly every single corner of Kharkiv and can tell you a lot about the history and architecture. Have fun on your kayak trip!
I hope we will see eachother again, safe travels Lili and Anthon:)

I came to Kharkiv to see a friend from France (he couldn't host me). Lili happened to know him, she found out about this before I came. That was a very fun coincidence! By the way, she is super fluent in French, and so is her boyfriend in Spanish. They were so nice. They met me at the train station. Also they have a cool flat in the center. On the first night, I spent some time with my friend whom I see once a year, he bought me back to their house, and we had some tea together. The second night we all went to an international pub, great one, with another person from CS who didn't work those days and who had showed me the city. So in this night I felt at home and surrounded by friends, it is a really great time I had in Kharkiv. The best ending I could have for this trip in Ukraine. On the last morning before I flew back to Paris, Lili showed me some streets, cafe and soup, it was really good. Thank you so much for your hospitality and for this time I had here. I hope we meet again :)

The words and pixels are not enough to describe Lili and Anthon, insted of 1 day instayed 5. they showed me whole Kharkiv, also they organized a travel presentation of my journey to Kharkiv Travel Club. Helped me with Everything.

Besides of perfect hosting rhey both are amazing, so sweet, kind, polite, friendly, relaxed. I am just fascinated by them. I really feelmthat i have friends for life now in Kharkiv!

text:
I didn't meet with Lili and i could be sad about that, but in somehow i feel like we will meet in future, in somewhere, so i am not sad, i am happy that i contacted with her.

It was my first couchsurfing experience as a surfer and i was in a country that i couldn't even read the alphabeth, also cause of i was travelling alone, I was worried about my travel. 
When i sent her a msg on CS, she told that she will be out of country but her boyfriend can help me. She was really thoughtful kind and caring me eventhough we didn't meet. I think, that is an amazing generous soul. 

Her boyfriend, Anton is also awesome btw, he guided me in city(not only knows but also loves  a lot about culture, history, architecture, food...). He brought me to many beautiful places where was impossible to find as a tourist. He answered all my questions eventhough they were stupid smtimes. I changed my staying plans not only once and he was pretty ok with that all the time, was in a good mood always that made me same as well.

If you would like to come ƒ∞stanbul, or whereever i am,  you will be always welcomed.
Wish you best!

Lili is an extremely kind and thoughtful host. She was keen to show me interesting and hidden parts of the city and we shared music from different cultures. Lili's travels are very interesting and she told about some of her exciting adventures. I was always greeted with a smile and I loved staying with her; I can't wait to meet again.

I stayed with Lili and Anton for three days and I had a wonderful (multilingual) time with them. We had very interesting discussions and Lili showed me around Kharkiv for an entire (very warm) day trying to avoid the sunny spots. Anton is an excellent tourist city guide and you just have to poke him slightly and stories about architecture and history will burst out of him. They are a lovely couple and very helpful and kind people. I can only recommend staying with them in Kharkiv at their construction site :). 

Dear Lili and Anton, I wish you good luck with your roof and the other parts of the flat. I‚Äôm sure it will be amazing once finished ‚Äì full of original Anton-lego-like architecture and Lili-like drawings on the walls. I really hope to see you again!

text:
Vika and her father Pavel were kind enough to invite me to their apartment and stay while I was in Kharkiv.

They were both very kind and hospitable and I really enjoyed my chats with her father.

Vika is an experienced couch surfer and an amazing tour guide. She took me around the city and showed me a many many places that I would never have found myself. 

Thank you both Pavel and Vika and see you next time in Kharkiv for a Metalist game!

Hmmmm...
Wierd,it is my first negative CS experience after 3+ years here :-(
But CS is all about occasoins, so I have to write it. Maybe it was just my bad luck. Who knows...

Vika invited me to surf her couch when I was posting some thread on Kharkiv group.
However when I came I found that the apartment was extremely dirty and messy.
My comfort standart is pretty low but still that was simply too much.
I had to move things on the floor in order to make some space for a matras.

Unfortunately I even didn't have a chance to drink a cup of tea when asked Vika to do so.
It was pretty late, I was tired after a long trip and hungry.

We didn't talk much as Vika was busy on her computer.

I wouldn't wish such situation even for an enemy.

Even though I didn't show to Vika directly that I didn't like it, in the morning I asked if that was a normal situation for her.
She asnwered: "Yes" :-(

Sorry, Vika, but that was negative CS experience, as for me...

text:
Vika is a friendly, helpful and social person. After my posting in the Kharkiv forum, that she moderate, about my search for an apartment, she answered, but also offered to host me for several days. Me and my CS-friend Vladimir surfed at Vika's place for one night, just before we find our own apartment on 'Prospect Peremohy' at Alekseevskaya Metro. We brought a grilled chicken with us the night we arrived, and we had a great talk during our late dinner. When I was settled I organized several couchsurfing meetings in Kharkiv that she all joined. The second event the "Kharkiv City Guide Game" we organized together . Vika did a very good job, and the event was successful. We had 7 teams. Unfortunately Vladimir, Vova and I only reached the 5th place.

During my visit Victoriya became the Kharkiv CS Ambassador. I wish her many success and pleasure to boost up the Kharkiv community.

UPDATE: It was a pleasure to meet Vika again in Simferopol on the Crimean Carnival.

do not hesitate to host

Andriy and George are the first father-and-son couch-surfers we have ever hosted in our two-year couch-surfing experience. Seeing the interaction between father and son for the first hand in our home, we admire as well as respect Andriy‚Äôs patience and dedication towards his son ‚Äî realising how important a trip can affect and improve relationship. George was shy in the beginning without speaking any word of English but slowly opened his heart as we interacted with each other more. Eventually, he not only communicated with us in English but also showed his age of naughtiness and boyishness! Andriy is a very kind, generous, and open-minded person who is willing to demonstrate his expertise as a computer engineer when one of us had the question of photography editing. They also came with us to attend our family party for Christmas. He also prepared the delicious breakfast and Ukrainian meals of the Borshch soup and the chicken stew for us. On the top of that, we shared and discussed various issues such as politics, food, culture, family, relationship as well as the difficult issue of immigration. They even came back again to stay with us for extra two nights after the incident of missing their scheduled flight. We had such a great time together during their stay. We wish in the near future we can visit Andriy and George in Ukraine, having fun and knowing more about the culture, society, people, food and many more!!!!
